    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import os, fem\n",
    "data_dir = '../../../../data/currency'"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7fc430553f10>"
      ]

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x = np.loadtxt(os.path.join(data_dir, 'currency_original.txt'), skiprows=1)[:,1:].T\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(x.shape[0], 1, figsize=(16,4))\n",
    "for i, xi in enumerate(x):\n",
    "    ax[i].plot(xi, 'k-')\n",
    "    ax[i].axis('off')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7fc43056aa90>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# dx_sign = np.array([xi > xi.mean() for xi in x]).astype(int)\n",
    "dx_sign = np.sign(np.diff(x, axis=1)).astype(int)\n",
    "dx_sign, cat_dx_sign = fem.discrete.fit.categorize(dx_sign)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(x.shape[0], 1, figsize=(16,4))\n",
    "for i, dxi in enumerate(dx_sign):\n",
    "    ax[i].plot(dxi[:500], 'k-')\n",
    "    ax[i].axis('off')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7fc3bd5e9ad0>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "w, d = fem.discrete.fit.fit(dx_sign[:,:-1], dx_sign[:,1:], degs=[1], overfit=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(8,4))\n",
    "for di in d:\n",
    "    ax[0].plot((di - di.min()) / (di.max() - di.min()), 'k-', lw=0.5)\n",
    "ax[0].set_xlabel('iteration')\n",
    "ax[0].set_ylabel('discrepancy')\n",
    "ax[1].matshow(w[1], cmap='seismic')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {

   ],
   "source": [
    "w, d = fem.discrete.fit.fit(dx_sign[:,:-1], dx_sign[:,1:], degs=[1, 2], overfit=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(12,4))\n",
    "for di in d:\n",
    "    ax[0].plot((di - di.min()) / (di.max() - di.min()), 'k-', lw=0.5)\n",
    "ax[0].set_xlabel('iteration')\n",
    "ax[0].set_ylabel('discrepancy')\n",
    "ax[1].matshow(w[1], cmap='seismic', aspect='auto')\n",
    "ax[2].matshow(w[2], cmap='seismic', aspect='auto')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "def predict(w, x, cat_x):\n",
    "    degs = np.sort(w.keys())\n",
    "    w = np.hstack(w.values())\n",
    "    x, idx = fem.discrete.fit.one_hot(x, degs=degs)\n",
    "    x = x.toarray()\n",
    "    m = np.cumsum([len(cat) for cat in cat_x[:-1]])\n",
    "    p = np.split(w.dot(x), m, axis=0)\n",
    "    x = np.array([pi.argmax(axis=0) for pi in p])\n",
    "    i = np.arange(x.shape[1])\n",
    "    p = np.array([pi[xi, i] for xi, pi in zip(x, p)])\n",
    "    return x, p\n",
    "\n",
    "# t0, tn, tw, dt = 0, dx_sign.shape[1], 20, 1\n",
    "# t1, t2 = t0, t0 + tw\n",
    "# while t2 < tn:\n",
    "#     w, d = fem.discrete.fit.fit(dx_sign[:,t1:t2], dx_sign[:,t1+1:t2+1], degs=[1], overfit=True)\n",
    "#     dx_sign_predict, p = predict(w, dx_sign[:,t2-1], cat_dx_sign)\n",
    "#     print p\n",
    "#     t1 += dt\n",
    "#     t2 = t1 + tw\n",
    "\n",
    "w, d = fem.discrete.fit.fit(dx_sign[:,:-1], dx_sign[:,1:], degs=[1], overfit=True)\n",
    "dx_sign_predict, p = predict(w, dx_sign, cat_dx_sign)\n",
    "print np.isclose(dx_sign[:,1:], dx_sign_predict[:,:-1]).mean()\n",
    "w, d = fem.discrete.fit.fit(dx_sign[:,:-1], dx_sign[:,1:], degs=[1,2], overfit=True)\n",
    "dx_sign_predict, p = predict(w, dx_sign, cat_dx_sign)\n",
    "print np.isclose(dx_sign[:,1:], dx_sign_predict[:,:-1]).mean()"
   ]
